@node "Future" "ZAPP - The Future"
              _____ _          ___     _                      
             |_   _| |_  ___  | __|  _| |_ _  _ _ _ ___       
               | | | ' \/ -_) | _| || |  _| || | '_/ -_)_ _ _ 
               |_| |_||_\___| |_| \_,_|\__|\_,_|_| \___(_|_|_)

   This is the first release of ZAPP and everything seems to be working
just fine.  I still have one or two improvements to the packet send/receive
mechanism that need implementing but they are just minor changes.

   I'm planning a zapplink.device for linking up ZAPP servers across a
dial-up line to allow users on one server to contact the users on the
others.

   I'm also planning a suite of new devices for ZAPP connections over the
InterNet.  This can be done at the moment with one of the many telnet
server packages that are available but it'll be slow!

   A PC version of the client software is being thought about but if anyone
has any insights as to how it would be accomplished then please get in
touch...  We might be interested in paying a good programmer to write it
for us too !

Client Improvements

 - ZNFS: Will have directory access protection.

 - ZNFS: Will have read/write access with byte restrictions.  A nice use of
         this would be SysOps offering each user X megs of local WWW space.

Planned Clients

 - TEMP: Copies a temporary file to the user/bbs for further processing.

 - EDIT: Calls the users local editor (Cygnus, Ed, etc) to edit a text
         file.  This can then be sent back to the BBS with the TEMP client.

 - VIEW: Calls some sort of MultiView type program.  For use with the TEMP
         client.

 - ZGUI: A GUI system!!  Forget ANSI interfaces: you'll be able to traverse
         the BBS with scalable, font adaptive, real-time, BOOPSI based GUI
         windows!  Hurrah!

Planned Add-Ons

 - A rexxzapp.library to give ARexx programmers the ability to write ZAPP
   clients.

@endnode

